Data Binding in LWC using @Track
---------------------------------

Scenario 	: Create a LWC to input a student name and their favourite subject. 


Step 1		:	Open Default org if not already done 


Step 2 		: 	Create A LWC

				ctrl+shift+p 	-> SFDX: Create Lightning Web Components	->		Enter File Name : Example = 'studentForm'  (Salesforce recommends "Camel Case" format)		->		Select Directory


Step 3 		: 	Edit studentForm.html

				- Create 2 tags to display properties. 
				- Create 2 lightning tags to input data and add their handler events.
						
								
Step 4 		: 	Edit studentForm.js

				- Add @track to properties
				- Create Handlers


Step 5 		: 	Edit studentForm.js-meta.xml file

				- Set is exposed to 'true'
				- Create and add the targets


Step 6 		: 	Push Source to Default Scratch Org

				ctrl+shift+p	->		SFDX: Push Source to Default Scratch Org
				
				
Step 7 		: 	Display LWC component on service app page


Step 8 		: 	Enter Data in the lightning-inputs to test component.


 
